## 7. Security Obligations

### AcmeCorp Obligations
- Maintain ISO 27001 and SOC 2 Type II (provide reports upon written request + NDA)
- Annual third-party penetration testing (summary available on request)
- Annual BCP/DR test (summary available on request)
- Encryption: TLS 1.2+ in transit, AES-256 at rest
- MFA on all administrative production access
- Quarterly access recertification for personnel with access to ContosoAI Data
- **Incident notification: within 48 hours** of confirming a breach involving ContosoAI Data

### ContosoAI Obligations
- Maintain confidentiality and security of all credentials/API keys
- **Notify AcmeCorp promptly** of any suspected unauthorized account access
- No penetration testing of Services without AcmeCorp's prior written consent

---

## 8. Data & Privacy

- **Data hosting:** US only (AWS us-west-2 and us-east-1); dedicated tenant with logically isolated storage
- **ContosoAI = Data Controller; AcmeCorp = Data Processor** (GDPR, CCPA)
- AcmeCorp processes ContosoAI Data only for service delivery, support, security, and legal compliance — never for AcmeCorp's own marketing
- **Sub-processor changes:** AcmeCorp must give **30 days' notice**; ContosoAI has **15 days** to object
- **On termination:** ContosoAI has **60 days** to export data in machine-readable format before secure deletion
- AcmeCorp must provide written certification of deletion upon request
- EEA/UK/Swiss data transfers governed by Standard Contractual Clauses (incorporated into DPA)

---

## 9. Intellectual Property

- AcmeCorp retains all IP in Services, Platform, Documentation, Updates, and Upgrades
- ContosoAI retains all IP in ContosoAI Data
- Custom SOW deliverables expressly assigned to ContosoAI in a SOW are owned by ContosoAI (subject to AcmeCorp license-back of embedded know-how)
- **Feedback:** ContosoAI grants AcmeCorp perpetual, royalty-free license to use any feedback for any purpose
- Third-party open-source component bill of materials available upon written request

